<h2>Rapid Descriptions</h2>
<div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView79' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid102304">Boulder Rapid</a></b> (Class III, Mile -122.0)<br>
<p>
River maintains class III character in a wide, open, twisting rapid.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView80' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2465">Fish Creek Put In</a></b> (Class N/A, Mile -120.3)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Fish Creek put-in</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1PhotoDetailView142' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/881609/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/881609.jpg">
</a>
<i>Fish Creek put-in</i></div><div>Photo by Thomas O'Keefe © taken 06/29/12 @ 5300 cfs</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>
Nice USFS put-in with raft slide.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView81' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2466">Fish Creek Rapid</a></b> (Class III, Mile -120.1)<br>
<p>
Long wide open twisting rapid with three parts and a major wave segment at the bottom around a left turn.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView82' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2467">Sandy Beach Rapid</a></b> (Class III, Mile -119.8)<br>
<p>
Popular play spot at lower water levels. Around sharp right bend adjacent to sandy beach.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView83' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid102302">Mile 119 Rapid</a></b> (Class III+, Mile -119.2)<br>
<p>
Short rapid with variety of features at varying water levels. Usually has large waves.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView84' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2468">Killer Fang Falls</a></b> (Class IV, Mile -119.1)<br>
<p>
Two large rocks on river left become holes, hydraulics, then huge crashing waves as water level rises. Shear rock on left with sneak on right at most levels.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView85' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid102303">Eel Creek Rapid</a></b> (Class III, Mile -118.8)<br>
<p>
Straight shot with some breaking waves at higher levels.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView86' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2469">Otter Slide Rapid</a></b> (Class III, Mile -118.1)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Otter Slide</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1PhotoDetailView146' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/874705/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/874705.jpg">
</a>
<i>Otter Slide</i></div><div>Photo taken 05/30/10 @ a good level</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>
Straight forward rapid whose low water holes become high water waves.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView87' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2470">Morning Glory Rapid</a></b> (Class IV, Mile -117.7)<br>
<p>
Hard left corner pushes water to outside of turn at high water. Low water chute down left is a fast ride with a big hole at the bottom.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView88' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2471">House Wave Rapid</a></b> (Class IV, Mile -117.0)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>House Wave</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1PhotoDetailView150' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/874701/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/874701.jpg">
</a>
<i>House Wave</i></div><div>Photo taken 05/30/10 @ a good level</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>
Forms one of the biggest waves on the river at high water. Backed by a series of waves.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView89' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2472">Bloody Mary Rapid</a></b> (Class IV, Mile -116.6)<br>
<p>
Big waves and an occasional hole. Watch for pourover on right shore.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView90' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2473">Grim Reaper Rapid</a></b> (Class IV, Mile -116.0)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>IK'ing Grim Reaper</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1PhotoDetailView154' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/282/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/282.jpg">
</a>
<i>IK'ing Grim Reaper</i></div><div>Photo by Nick Borelli taken 07/15/99 @ 7000</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>
Changeable rapid with varying features. Pushy water with lots of side action and a big pour-over on the bottom left. More technical at lower flows.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView91' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2474">Cliffside Rapid</a></b> (Class III, Mile -115.6)<br>
<p>
Under mossy granite cliffs. Washes out at higher levels. Surfing waves at lower levels.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView92' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2475">Shoestring Falls Rapid</a></b> (Class IV, Mile -115.3)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>shoestring</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1PhotoDetailView158' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/11311/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/11311.jpg">
</a>
<i>shoestring</i></div><div>Photo taken 05/15/05 @ 7000 cfs</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>
Big waves at high water give way to smaller more technical drop at lower levels.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView93' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2476">Jones's Wave Rapid</a></b> (Class IV, Mile -115.1)<br>
<p>
Chains of waves that increase in size with rising water levels. Can cause problems at higher levels due to side action.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView94' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2477">Horsetail Falls</a></b> (Class IV, Mile -114.6)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Horsetail Falls</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1PhotoDetailView162' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/874693/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/874693.jpg">
</a>
<i>Horsetail Falls</i></div><div>Photo taken 05/30/10 @ a good level</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>
Rocks begin to emerge making this a technical drop at lower water and a mixmaster of side currents at higher levels.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView95' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2478">Prelude Rapid</a></b> (Class IV, Mile -114.4)<br>
<p>
At higher levels curling and breaking waves continue to the next rapid. The rapid begins to disappear at lower levels.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView96' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2479">Lochsa Falls</a></b> (Class IV+, Mile -114.2)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Lochsa Falls Dishing It Out</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1PhotoDetailView166' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/18424/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/18424.jpg">
</a>
<i>Lochsa Falls Dishing It Out</i></div><div>Photo of Dan Berger by Mamie Smith taken Cinco de Mayo</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>
A very short rapid with a falls-like vertical drop. Left side ledge becomes a large pour over then a crashing wave at higher levels. Right side tongue is navigable at most levels. A popular viewing spot and landmark at the mile 114.2 pullout.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView97' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid102305">Picking up the Pieces</a></b> (Class III+, Mile -113.9)<br>
<p>
Continuous series of waves with few obstructions. Grows as water level increases.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView98' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2480">Pipeline Rapid</a></b> (Class III+, Mile -113.6)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Anett at Pipeline</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1PhotoDetailView170' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/881611/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/881611.jpg">
</a>
<i>Anett at Pipeline</i></div><div>Photo of Anett Trebitz by Thomas O'Keefe © taken 06/29/12 @ 5300 cfs</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>
Classic park and play spot with large waves for surfing and playing.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView99' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2481">Old Man Rapid</a></b> (Class IV, Mile -113.3)<br>
<p>
Straightforward rapid. Some holes and obstacles left and right. Old Man Creek enters river left.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView100' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2482">Termination Rapid</a></b> (Class IV, Mile -112.8)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Termination</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1PhotoDetailView174' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/874683/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/874683.jpg">
</a>
<i>Termination</i></div><div>Photo taken 05/30/10 @ a good level</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>
Rapid terminates against a cliff wall at the bottom. Usually no trouble avoiding it although the large V wave is quite pushy at high water.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1RiverRapidView101' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid2483">Split Creek Rapid</a></b> (Class IV, Mile -111.7)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Split Creek Rapid</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqmtl5t3jlmte1PhotoDetailView178' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/881616/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/881616.jpg">
</a>
<i>Split Creek Rapid</i></div><div>Photo by Thomas O'Keefe © taken 06/29/12 @ 5300 cfs</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
<p>
Large waves and holes left and right with a route down the middle at most flows. Holes can be quite deceiving hiding behind waves.</p>
<br>
<br clear=right>
</div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
